# Design Tokens First

- Use Workday Canvas tokens as the source of truth for color, depth, and interaction layers.
- Define app semantic aliases (for example: `--color-action`, `--color-info`, `--color-surface`) and map them to Canvas tokens.
- Prefer system tokens before brand tokens for application-wide consistency.
- Keep accent colors sparse and purpose-driven; use neutral surfaces for layout containers.

## Do

- Use token variables in CSS and component styles.
- Create shared aliases in one central tokens file.

## Don't

- Do not hardcode hex/rgb/oklch values in feature components.
- Do not invent one-off color meanings that conflict with action/info/success/warning/danger semantics.
